articles.title: Asia markets trade mostly higher after Wall Street extends gains on hopes of softer Trump tariffs - CNBC
articles.description: Asia-Pacific markets open higher on Wednesday, tracking gains on Wall Street.
articles.content:
Asia-Pacific markets traded higher Wednesday, tracking Wall Street gains on expectations that U.S. President Donald Trump's tariffs could be softer than expected earlier.
